        <h3>Document Security and Coordination</h3>
        <p>Your original documents travel through multiple authorities across two countries. We coordinate secure handling at every stepâ€”from collection in Pakistan through HEC/IBCC verification, MOFA Pakistan attestation, UAE Embassy Islamabad, and finally MOFA in Dubai. Each handoff is tracked with confirmation. Documents pass through encrypted communication channels for status updates. Our Pakistan-based agents maintain direct relationships with attestation authorities, enabling faster processing and immediate issue resolution. For professionals already in UAE, we coordinate the entire Pakistan-side process remotelyâ€”no need to travel back for attestation. Confidential documents (employment records, professional registrations, family certificates) receive appropriate handling discretion throughout the chain.</p>

        <h3>HEC Attestation Requirements and Process</h3>
        <p>The <strong>Higher Education Commission (HEC)</strong> is the regulatory body for all universities in Pakistan. HEC attestation confirms that a degree was genuinely issued by a recognized Pakistani university. The attestation process requires: original degree certificate, original transcript, copy of CNIC (Computerized National Identity Card), and applicable fees. HEC maintains offices in Islamabad (main office), Karachi, Lahore, Peshawar, and Quetta. Processing typically takes 3-5 working days at the main Islamabad office. Regional offices may have longer processing times during peak periods. HEC verification can also be done online through the HEC portal, but the physical attestation stamp is required for MOFA Pakistan processing. Fake degree detection has become stricterâ€”HEC cross-verifies with university records before attestation. Degrees from unrecognized institutions are not attested. Our agents verify HEC recognition status before submission to prevent rejection.</p>

        <h3>IBCC Equivalence for School Certificates</h3>
        <p>The <strong>Inter Board Committee of Chairmen (IBCC)</strong> issues equivalence certificates for matriculation (SSC) and intermediate (HSSC) qualifications. IBCC equivalence is mandatory for school certificates before MOFA Pakistan will attest. The equivalence certificate confirms the qualification level and subjects completed. Processing requires: original certificates from the respective education board, mark sheets, and applicable fees. IBCC has offices in Islamabad and regional centers. Processing time is typically 5-7 working days. For students with O-Levels or A-Levels from British curriculum schools in Pakistan, IBCC equivalence converts these qualifications to the Pakistani grading system. Cambridge and Edexcel certificates require IBCC equivalence before attestation. Our agents coordinate IBCC processing as part of the complete attestation chain.</p>

        <h3>UAE Embassy Islamabad and Consulates</h3>
        <p>The <strong>UAE Embassy in Islamabad</strong> is located at Diplomatic Enclave, Ramna 5. Operating hours are Sunday to Thursday, 8:30 AM to 2:30 PM. The embassy handles document attestation for documents from Punjab, KPK, Islamabad, and Northern Areas. The <strong>UAE Consulate in Karachi</strong> handles Sindh and Balochistan documents, located at Block 9, Clifton. Processing time at both locations is typically 5-7 working days. Embassy attestation requires prior MOFA Pakistan stampâ€”documents without MOFA Pakistan authentication are rejected. Fee payment is required at submission. Express services may be available for urgent requirements. Our agents in both Islamabad and Karachi maintain regular submission schedules to ensure efficient processing. The embassy may request additional documentation for commercial documents or powers of attorneyâ€”we verify all requirements before submission.</p>

        <h3>NADRA Documents for Personal Records</h3>
        <p><strong>NADRA (National Database and Registration Authority)</strong> issues birth certificates, marriage registration certificates, and other civil status documents through its Family Registration Certificate (FRC) system. NADRA-issued documents go directly to MOFA Pakistan without HEC or IBCC verification. However, documents must be genuine NADRA-issued certificatesâ€”local union council certificates require verification from the issuing authority first. NADRA offices across Pakistan can issue certified copies of birth and marriage records. For marriages performed abroad, NADRA marriage registration requires documentation from the foreign country. Nikah Nama (Islamic marriage contract) from registered Nikah Khawan can be attested after MOFA Pakistan verification. Our agents advise on document-specific requirements based on issuing authority and document type.</p>

