          <h3>Why is HEC attestation mandatory for Pakistani degrees?</h3>
          <p>HEC attestation confirms that your degree was issued by a recognized Pakistani university and is genuine. Under Article 10 of the HEC Ordinance 2002, HEC is the sole authority for degree verification in Pakistan. Without HEC attestation, MOFA Pakistan will not attest educational documents, and UAE authorities will reject employment visa applications. HEC maintains records of all recognized institutions and cross-verifies degrees with university registrar records before attestation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What is the difference between IBCC equivalence and attestation?</h3>
          <p>IBCC equivalence converts your school qualification to a standardized Pakistani grading format recognized internationally. Attestation confirms the document is genuine. Both are required for matriculation and intermediate certificates. IBCC first verifies your qualification with the issuing education board, issues an equivalence certificate, and then attests both documents. O-Level and A-Level certificates from British curriculum schools require IBCC equivalence before attestation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I get attestation from UAE Embassy Karachi if my documents are from Punjab?</h3>
