        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How long does the complete Pakistan attestation chain take?</h3>
          <p>The complete attestation chain typically takes 15-20 working days: HEC/IBCC verification (5-7 days), MOFA Pakistan attestation (3-5 days), UAE Embassy/Consulate legalization (5-7 days), and MOFA UAE attestation (2-3 days after document arrives in Dubai). Express services can reduce total time. Processing may extend during peak employment seasons, particularly September through November when new visa cycles begin.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Do medical professionals need PMDC verification in addition to HEC?</h3>
          <p>Yes. <strong>PMDC (Pakistan Medical and Dental Council)</strong> verification is required for all medical professionals alongside HEC attestation. PMDC confirms your registration status and good standing. For <a href="/specialized/medical/dha-dataflow/">DHA licensing</a> in Dubai, you need: PMDC registration certificate, PMDC good standing certificate, HEC-attested MBBS/BDS degree, and completed DataFlow verification. Nursing professionals need Pakistan Nursing Council (PNC) verification instead of PMDC.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What if my degree is from an unrecognized university?</h3>
          <p>HEC does not attest degrees from unrecognized institutions. If your university has lost HEC recognition or was never recognized, attestation is not possible. HEC maintains a list of recognized universities on its website. Some institutions have conditional recognitionâ€”verify your university's status before starting the attestation process. If your institution has recognition issues, contact HEC directly for guidance on degree verification options.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I process attestation while working in UAE?</h3>
          <p>Yes. Our agents in Islamabad, Karachi, and Lahore handle the complete Pakistan-side attestation while you remain in UAE. You can courier original documents to our agents or authorize a family member to submit on your behalf. We provide secure tracking throughout the process. Once documents complete UAE Embassy attestation in Pakistan, they are couriered to UAE for MOFA completion and delivery to your location.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Is translation required for Pakistani documents in UAE?</h3>
          <p>Most Pakistani educational documents are issued in English and do not require translation. However, some documents include Urdu text that may require <a href="/services/legal-translation/">MOJ-certified translation</a>. Nikah Nama (marriage certificate) is often in Urdu and requires translation for UAE spouse visa applications. NADRA documents are typically bilingual (English and Urdu). We advise on translation requirements based on your specific documents and intended use.</p>
